## 9. Complaints

If you believe we have breached your privacy, you may:

1. Contact us directly using the details in Section 8.
2. Lodge a complaint with the **Office of the Australian Information Commissioner (OAIC)** at [www.oaic.gov.au](https://www.oaic.gov.au).

---

## 10. Notifiable Data Breaches

{% if revenue_exceeds_threshold or trades_in_personal_info %}
{{ business_name }} is required to comply with the Notifiable Data Breaches (NDB) scheme. If we become aware of an eligible data breach involving AI systems, we will:

1. Assess the breach as quickly as practicable, and within 30 days of becoming aware of grounds to suspect a breach (s 26WH, Privacy Act 1988).
2. Notify the OAIC and affected individuals if the assessment confirms a risk of serious harm.
3. Take remedial action to prevent further breaches.
{% else %}
While the NDB scheme currently applies to organisations covered by the Privacy Act, {{ business_name }} voluntarily follows NDB procedures as best practice.
{% endif %}

